[In the past 24 hours, 10 countries: the USA (103 143), Germany (38 664), Taiwan (45 100), Brazil (40 173), Argentina (36 835), North Korea (32 810), the UK (28 231), Australia (26 156), Japan (23 332), and Italy (10 668), reported the highest numbers of cases, all reporting more than 10 000 newly confirmed cases. A global total of 1008 deaths were reported in the preceding 24 hours (late 11 Jun 2022 to late 12 Jun 2022).

A total of 33 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours; 15 of the 33 countries are from the European region, 7 are from the Americas region, 2 from the Eastern Mediterranean region, 6 are from the Western Pacific region, 2 are from the South East Asia region, and 1 are from the African region.

Comparing the 7-day averages of daily confirmed cases from the past 7 days and those from 8-14 days ago, case counts have increased by 28.8%, while daily reported deaths have increased by 2%. Comparative 7-day averages in the USA show 23.5% increase in daily reported cases and 13.2% increase in reported deaths.

Impression: The global daily reported over 0.48 million newly confirmed infections in the past 24 hours with over 541.03 million cumulative reported cases and over 6.33 million reported deaths. - Mod.UBA]
